'''Anastasia Heonis''' is a model also known as "'''Acid PopTart'''." [[Joe Corroney]], who once shared an apartment with her,<ref name="Facebook 1">{{Facebook|username=theAcidPopTart|url=photos/10155418701271531|name=Acid PopTart|date=June 14, 2017|quote=That time an awesome artist and long ago flat mate chose me to be the model for Ailyn Vel, the daughter of Boba Fett. Character created by Abel G. Peña and illustrated by @joecorroney. I'm proudly in the Wookiepedia as well.|archivedate=20211125183023}}</ref> used her as inspiration for the illustration of two characters: [[Thrynka Padaunete]].<ref name="Facebook 2">{{Facebook|username=theAcidPopTart|url=photos/251913361530|name=Acid PopTart|date=January 12, 2010|quote=Myself modeling for Thrynka, a leader of the Rebel Alliance, for yes, freakin' Star Wars. Joe is awesome, I know all sorts of hilarious secrets about him, but he paid me off with feeding my ego and drawing me. Damn him.<br />Appeared in SW Insider #71<br />Based off a photo Laura Dark took of me<br />Art is by Joe Corroney and you should check him out|archivedate=20211125182852}}</ref> and [[Ailyn Vel]].<ref name="Facebook 3">{{Facebook|username=theAcidPopTart|url=photos/317840561530|name=Acid PopTart|date=February 19, 2010|quote=I was beyond geeked to be used as the model, by the talented Joe Corroney, for the newly created character, Ailyn Vel from the Star Wars Universe. Little secret: Joe and I go way back with many great talks, one being my belief that Boba Fett (my second fav character) was actually a female, a spurn lover, after Han Solo. Ailyn Vel is in fact, Boba Fett's daughter, and she's after her father with a serious vengeance now. When I got the low down on the character, I was so squeeing with delight. THANKS JOE!!! Based off a photo taken by Jason Perlman. (Appeared in Star Wars Insider Magazine)|archivedate=20211125182903}}</ref> The former was based of photography by Laura Dark,<ref name="Facebook 2" /> and was featured in [[Star Wars Insider 71|''Star Wars Insider'' 71]],<ref name="Insider 71">[[Star Wars Insider 71|''Star Wars Insider'' 71]]</ref> while the latter was based of a photography by Jason Perlman,<ref name="Facebook 3" /> and appeared in [[Star Wars Insider 80|''Star Wars Insider'' 80]].<ref name="Insider 80">[[Star Wars Insider 80|''Star Wars Insider'' 80]]</ref>

